    "content": "---\nname: Pipeline architecture and component registry\ndescription: Overview of the multimodal RAG benchmark pipeline — components, registry pattern, data flow, and what's been built\ntype: project\n---\n\n5-stage pipeline: Load Dataset → Build Retrieval Index → Load Model → Retrieve+Generate+Evaluate per sample → Aggregate Results.\n\nAll components use @register_* decorator pattern. Adding new components = subclass base + register.\n\n**Datasets (pipeline/datasets/):** hotpotqa, docvqa, gqa\n**Retrievers (pipeline/retrieval/):**\n- Custom (in-memory): bm25, dense, clip\n- Production (persistent): dense_qdrant (Qdrant), clip_qdrant (Qdrant), bm25_elastic (Elasticsearch)\n- Production retrievers namespace index/collection per dataset: e.g. `dense_text_hotpotqa`, `bm25_text_docvqa`\n\n**Models (pipeline/models/):** gpt, gemini, gemini_vertex, qwen_vl\n- gemini uses google.genai SDK (not deprecated google.generativeai)\n- qwen_vl_aws planned but waiting on company AWS endpoint confirmation\n\n**Evaluation (pipeline/evaluation/):**\n- Custom backend (default): retrieval_metrics.py, answer_metrics.py, grounding_metrics.py, multimodal_metrics.py\n- Production backend: retrieval_metrics_ranx.py (ranx), answer_metrics_hf.py (HF evaluate), grounding_metrics_ragas.py (RAGAS LLM-as-judge)\n- Backend selected via config: evaluation.backend: \"custom\" | \"production\"\n\n**Why:** How to apply: Use this to orient quickly at session start — read the relevant file rather than re-deriving structure.\n"
  },
