    "content": "---\nname: Design principles the user enforces\ndescription: Explicit design rules the user has corrected or confirmed — modular design, no file replacement, consistency\ntype: feedback\n---\n\nKeep the modular registry/factory pattern everywhere. New components = new file + subclass base + @register_* decorator. Never merge two components into one file.\n\n**Why:** User explicitly enforced this multiple times (\"dont replace any file, keep the modular design consistent and add separate files\").\n\n**How to apply:** When adding a new retriever/model/dataset/metric — always create a new file, never modify an existing implementation file to absorb it.\n\n---\n\nProduction-level libraries (ranx, HF evaluate, RAGAS) go in *separate* files alongside the custom implementations, not replacing them.\n\n**Why:** User said \"dont replace any file\" when asked about upgrading metrics to production libraries.\n\n**How to apply:** Custom files stay. New `_ranx`, `_hf`, `_ragas` suffixed files added alongside. Evaluator selects via config backend key.\n\n---\n\nDo not re-index if already indexed. Production retrievers (Qdrant, Elasticsearch) must skip encoding/indexing when the index already exists with the correct count.\n\n**Why:** Encoding is expensive. User confirmed this is the expected production behaviour.\n\n**How to apply:** All production retriever index() methods check existence before rebuilding.\n",
    "structuredPatch": [],
    "originalFile": null
  },
